-*-text-*-
NEWS  ---  History of user-visible changes.
Copyright (C)  2002  Marco Parrone.
See the end for copying conditions.

* Changes in mptris 1.9

** Added difficulty level selection.

Now it is possible to select among 10 different level of hardness, so
it is possible to win sometimes.

** Added support for command line options.

Command line options are not ignored now, and, among the others, the
options "--help" ("-h") and "--version" ("-V") are supported.

** Added better error checking, handling and reporting.

Now error messages are compliant with the GNU Coding Standards.

** Added Gnits compliant build system.

Now the distribution is Gnits compliant and uses GNU autoconf, GNU
automake, GNU autoheader, GNU aclocal, ecc...

** Added online NON-warranty and distributing conditions detail.

Now it is possible to read the relative parts of the GNU GPL from
mptris.

** mptris now is internazionalized.

mptris was internazionalized using GNU gettext.

** Added Italian localization.

An Italian localization was added.

** Added documentation.

Now the online documentation is better.  A manpage (made with
help2man) was added too.

** Removed the GUI.

I've not enought time to update it to the recent changes, it will
likely be re-added in a future version.

** Bug fixes.

The code now is cleaner, more tested and so there are less bugs.

